menu "breadboard: bb_ota_boot"

config BB_OTA_BOOT_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-register the OTA boot-mode HTTP route via bb_registry"
    default y if BB_OTA_STRATEGY_BOOT
    default n
    help
        When enabled, bb_ota_boot self-registers a single lean route
        (POST /api/update/apply) through bb_registry. The route only arms a
        one-shot NVS flag and reboots — the manifest resolve + firmware
        download happen at full heap on the next boot (bb_ota_boot_run_if_pending).
        This is the cheap trigger for tight / serial-less single-core boards
        that cannot afford bb_ota_pull's full route set at runtime. Defaults on
        only when the OTA strategy is boot-mode (see BB_OTA_STRATEGY), so
        /api/update/apply has a single owner — bb_ota_pull does not register it
        on a boot-mode board. Disable to keep the public C API but register the
        route manually or skip it.

endmenu
